<H3>Employer Training Assistance Program/Individual Training Assistance Program</H3>

Administered through Prairie State 2000, a state agency, these 
programs invest in training to upgrade the skills of workers presently 
employed by a company incorporating technological or productivity/quality 
changes in the workplace.  The programs are designed to assist in job 
retention through skills upgrading.  Funds are awarded through two programs 
-- the Employer Training Assistance Program and the Individual Training 
Assistance Program.  Grants and loans are available to Illinois businesses 
based on financial need and the type of retraining planned.  Funds may be 
used to pay for trainer costs, materials and supplies.<P>


