<H3>Workforce Preparation Grants</H3>

Thirty-eight Illinois public community college districts receive 
workforce preparation grants to operate business centers that provide 
training and services to businesses and cooperate with other local economic 
development entities to help attract and retain commerce and industry.  
Funds may be used to conduct a wide variety of job training and economic 
development activities, including customized job training for businesses, 
entrepreneurship training and services, contract procurement consulting 
services, business retention and job training for unemployed individuals.<P>


