<H3>School-to-Work Opportunities</H3>

Under the School-to-Work Opportunities Act, students choose a "career 
path" before entering the 11th grade.  Students make these decisions with 
the help of labor market information and career guidance and counseling.  
The network of One-Stop Career Centers (see Job Training Partnership Act, 
above) will be instrumental in providing students with the data they need 
to make informed decisions. <P>

