<h3>
Department of Commerce & Community Affairs<p>
</h3>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<FONT SIZE=+3>Workforce Development Programs</FONT>
<HR>

<H3>Enterprise Zones</H3>

There are 91 Enterprise Zones in Illinois which offer businesses a 
number of state and local incentives to encourage job creation or retention 
within their communities.  Among the incentives is the Enterprise Zone Jobs 
Tax Credit.  This credit allows a business a $500 credit on Illinois income 
taxes for each job created in an Enterprise Zone for which a certified 
dislocated worker or economically-disadvantaged individual is hired.  The 
credit may be carried forward for up to five years.  A minimum of five 
eligible employees must be hired to qualify for the credit.<P>

<HR>
<strong>| <a href="http://www.ilcommerce.com">DCCA Home Page</a> | <a href="/dcca/files/wforce/work.htm">Workforce Development</a> |</strong>

