<font size=+3>Energy, Coal & Recycling Programs</font>
<br clear=right>
<hr>

<CENTER><H3>School Education Program</H3></CENTER>
<HR>

<h3>Purpose</h3>

To support the education of Illinois' young people concerning recycling and waste reduction through funding for school recycling programs, teacher training, and curriculum development.<p>

<h3>Eligibility</h3>

Regional offices of Education, individual School Districts with more over 2,000 students enrolled, and six Chicago Public School Regions (School District #299).<p>

<h3>Funding</h3>

Funding is provided through a competitive grant round process.  Entities submitting an application may request funds to (1) purchase recycling related collection containers and equipment for school recycling programs; (2) implements source reduction activities; (3) promote classroom education efforts.  The amount of funding that may be requested is dependent upon the total number of students enrolled in the participating school(s), but may not exceed $35,000.  No applicant investment is required.<p>

<h3>Further Information</h3>

For further information, contact: Bina Fleck, School Education Program, Bureau of Energy and Recycling, Illinois Department of Commerce and Community Affairs at 217/785-3970.  TDD customers may call 217/785-0211.<p>


