<HEAD><TITLE>DCCA: Recycling and Waste Reduction Programs</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000080" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#8080C0" ALINK="#8080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/logosm.jpg" alt="DCCA Logo" width=165 height=82 align=left>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<h3>
Department of Commerce & Community Affairs<p>
</h3>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<font size=+3>Energy, Coal & Recycling Programs</font>
<br clear=right>
<hr>

<CENTER><H3>Illinois College Assistance Program for Recycling (I-CAP)</H3></CENTER>
<HR>

<h3>Purpose</h3>

To assist public universities and community colleges in the development and implementation of their legislative-mandated waste reduction plans.<p>

<h3>Eligibility</h3>

State-supported colleges and universities<p>

<h3>Funding</h3>

Funding is provided through a grant process.  Separate funding assistance is available for both development of the waste reduction plans and for implementation of activities outlined in approved waste reduction plans.  Supportable categories for implementation grants include collection, processing, composting and source reduction.  Maximum eligible amount of funding is dependent upon full time equivalent student population.<p>

<h3>Further Information</h3>

For further information, contact: Reg Willis, Program Management Section, Bureau of Energy and Recycling, Illinois Department of Commerce and Community Affairs at 217/785-2800.  TDD customers may call 217/785-0211.<p>


