<HEAD><TITLE>DCCA: Just for Kids -- Camp Keep</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#0000A0" LINK="#0000A0" VLINK="#FF0000" ALINK="#FF0000">

<img src="/dcca/graph/logosm.jpg" alt="DCCA Logo" width=165 height=82 align=left>

<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<h3>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs</h3>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4>


<img src="/dcca/graph/hugtrees.gif" width=185 height=232 align=right>
<h3 align=center>
Illinois Energy Education Development (ILEED) Program<br>
Introduces<p>

<hr width=50% align=center size=3>
CAMP KEEP<br>
JULY 20-27, 1997
<hr width=50% align=center size=3>
<br clear=all>

<p>
KIDS FOR ENERGY AND ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION<br>
CAMP C.I.L.C.A. SITE<br>
CANTRALL, IL<br>
<em>(located 10 miles northwest of Springfield)</em>
</h3>
<hr>
ILEED has proven to be an effective energy and environmental education program for Illinois' K-12 schools which uses a thematic approach to education that incorporated all disciplines.<p>

Through each element of the program, ILEED has promoted educational excellence, encouraged the students' imagination and creativity, developed students' organizational and leadership skills, and taught students to succeed.<p>

Kids for Energy and Environmental Protection Go to Camp!<p>

ILEED students are continuing to lead the way to Camp KEEP, for a week of energy and environmental discovery.  Experienced ILEED students will organize and conduct all camp activities.<p>

Participation in Camp KEEP is being offered to students who have completed grades 5-8 by June 1997.  Reservations are limited to the first 50 applicants.<p>

Camp KEEP will be held at the air conditioned Camp C.I.L.C.A. facilities located in a woods surrounding a lake near Cantrall, Illinois.  Campers will be housed in retreat centers and sleep on bunk beds.  Shower facilities are located in the centers.  A detailed information packet will be mailed after receiving your refundable deposit.<p>


<h3>CAMPERS WILL:</h3>
<ul type=square>
<li>Investigate Illinois' natural resources<p>
<li>Consider all aspects of the energy and environmental issues facing their generation<p>
<li>Learn to appreciate their unique talents and those of others, and<p>
<li>HAVE FUN!
</ul>


<h3>CAMP KEEP ACTIVITIES INCLUDE:</h3>
<ul type=square>
<li>Energy and Environmental related presentations<p>
<li>Hands-on Activities<p>
<li>Recreation Time - Supervised Swimming, Hiking, Canoeing, Paddle Boats<p>
</ul>


<h3>CAMP KEEP HAS THE FOLLOWING PERSONNEL ON SITE</h3>
<ul type=square>
<li>Adult Camp Director<p>
<li>2 Student Counselors for every 10 campers<p>
<li>1 Adult Mentor for every 2 Student Counselors<p>
<li>Camp Staff includes certified: cook, lifeguard, health care professional<p>
</ul>


<h3>What is the COST?</h3>

The cost for Camp KEEP is $175 all inclusive, plus campers provide their own transportation.  A $25 deposit is due with your application.<p>


<h3>How do I apply for Camp KEEP?</h3>

Camp KEEP is being offered to Illinois schools exclusively.  To be sure to reserve your space, call 217/785-3411 (TDD 217/785-0211) for your application.  Or write to:<p>
<dl><dd>
Camp KEEP - DCCA<br>
325 West Adams, Room 300<br>
Springfield, IL 62704-1892<br>
</dd></dl>


<hr>
<center>| <a href="http://www.ilcommerce.com"> DCCA Home</a> | <a href="/dcca/menus/kids.htm"> Just for Kids</a> |</center>

</h4>
