<h2>Services Offered</h2><dl>
<p><dt><strong>General Business Management Services</strong><dd>SBDC:  As a Small Business Development Center, this organization provides businesses with a wide range of general business management services.  They can assist you with the development of your business plan.  They can help you define your marketing objectives and approaches.  They work with you to improve your business ownership skills and show you how to analyze your business finances.  The SBDC will also help you access other specialized services such as export assistance or government marketing expertise and information.<p>For more information contact  Alan F. Hauff at (618) 692-2929
<p><dt><strong>International Trade Assistance</strong><dd>ITC:  As an International Trade Center, this organization can provide services related to the development of foreign markets for Illinois business products and services.  They may be able to help you identify your company's potential foreign markets.  They can then guide you through the many requirements of the both the U. S. and foreigh governments with respect to trade.<p>For more information contact Theresa Menk at (618) 692-2929
</dl><hr>
