<h3>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs<p></h3>
<img src="http://www.ilcommerce.com/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4>
<img src="http://www.ilcommerce.com/graph/sbdc3.gif" alt="SBDC Logo" width=200 height=160 align=right>
<p>
<center><h1>College of DuPage</h1></center><hr>
<p><a href="http://www.cod.edu">Our home page is here.</a><hr>
<strong>College of DuPage</strong><br>22nd and Lambert Road<br>Glen Ellyn, IL 60137<hr>
<h2>Services Offered</h2><dl>
<p><dt><strong>General Business Management Services</strong><dd>SBDC:  As a Small Business Development Center, this organization provides businesses with a wide range of general business management services.  They can assist you with the development of your business plan.  They can help you define your marketing objectives and approaches.  They work with you to improve your business ownership skills and show you how to analyze your business finances.  The SBDC will also help you access other specialized services such as export assistance or government marketing expertise and information.<p>For more information contact David Gay at (630) 942-2771.
<p><dt><strong>Government Procurement Assistance</strong><dd>PTAC:  This organization provides specialized services to Illinois businesses that want to do business with government at any level - local, state or federal.  As a Procurement Technical Assistance Center, they will provide general counseling in government procurement practices to help you sell your products or services.  They will help you identify government markets.  They can show you where to access bid specifications and help you review bid packages.  They can also provide information about contract administration and other contracting assistance services.<p>For more information contact Duffy Toler at (630) 942-2184.
<p><dt><strong>International Trade Assistance</strong><dd>ITC:  As an International Trade Center, this organization can provide services related to the development of foreign markets for Illinois business products and services.  They may be able to help you identify your company's potential foreign markets.  They can then guide you through the many requirements of the both the U. S. and foreigh governments with respect to trade.<p>For more information contact Shannon Rielly at (630) 942-3052.
</dl><hr>
