<h3>FORTUNE 500 LISTS 40 ILLINOIS FIRMS</h3>

Illinois companies were well represented in Fortune magazine's 1996 rankings of the largest U.S. industrial and service corporations with 40 firms located in the state.  Once again Illinois placed third for headquarters locations and Chicago ranked second among the cities with 17 firms.  While the state's 40 companies represented 8 percent of the Fortune 500 total, they garnered 8.4 percent of total sales and 10.6 percent of total profits.<p> 

