<hr>
<h3>CHICAGO METRO AREA # 1 IN 1995 NEW/EXPANDED FACILITIES</h3>

Site Selection magazine reported that "Chicago's on a tear, racking up the highest count of new facilities and expansions during 1995 than any other U.S. metro area," in their annual tally of corporate projects.  The city was described as "the runaway winner among all U.S. metros" with 265 new and expanded facilities last year.  Chicago attracted 101 new manufacturing plants in 1995 lead by the Chicago Recycling Corporation's $250 million facility.  Blue Cross & Blue Shield of Illinois also added to the growth with its new $200 million headquarters.<p>

The large Chicago metro total boosted Illinois' ranking to fifth among the states with 451 new corporate facilities and expansions last year.  It also placed fourth with 142 new manufacturing plants in the state during 1995.  The magazine noted the significance of Illinois' new tort reform measures in attracting businesses.  It also included reference to the state's skilled workforce, central location, highly developed infrastructure (world's busiest airport, etc.) and advanced information technologies.<p>


TOP 10 METRO AREAS IN 1995<br>
NEW/EXPANDED CORPORATE FACILITIES<p>
