<h3>Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) </h3>

<strong>ACCESS EPA:  An Environmental Directory</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://earth1.epa.gov/Access">http://earth1.epa.gov/Access/</a><p>

This is a directory of U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) and other
public sector environmental information resources.  <p>

<strong>Envirofacts</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.epa.gov/docs/enviro/html/ef_home.html">http://www.epa.gov/docs/enviro/html/ef_home.html/</a><p>

A U.S. EPA relational database that integrates data from four major EPA
program systems: permit compliance system (PCS), CERCLIS, TRIS, RCRIS. <p> 

<strong>EnviroSense</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://es.inel.gov">http://es.inel.gov/</a><p> 

The U.S. EPA's pollution prevention forum for all levels of government,
researchers, industry, and public interest groups.  Includes Solvent Umbrella, a solvent alternative information guide, and ASK EPA, an interactive forum for P2 questions. <p>

<strong>U.S. EPA Atmospheric Pollution Prevention Division</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.epa.gov/docs/GCDOAR/OAR-APPD.html">http://www.epa.gov/docs/GCDOAR/OAR-APPD.html</a><p>

Information on energy efficiency and P2 programs (e.g., Green Lights and
Energy Star programs); also contains information on Methane Outreach programs; fact sheets and publications listing are available.<p>

<strong>U.S. EPA Gopher Server</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="gopher://gopher.epa.gov">gopher://gopher.epa.gov/</a><p>

A listing of U.S. EPA's gopher resources.<p>

<strong>U.S. EPA WWW Server</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.epa.gov">http://www.epa.gov/</a><p>

Contains basic information about the EPA, press releases, EPA Journal, a
calender of events, etc.<p>

<strong>U.S. EPA's Air Pollution Database--AIRS</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.epa.gov/docs/airs/airs.html">http://www.epa.gov/docs/airs/airs.html</a><p>

Contains several databases with information about air pollution in the United States and various World Health Organization (WHO) member countries.<p>

<strong>SAGE--Solvent Alternatives Guide (U.S. EPA)</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://clean.rti.org">http://clean.rti.org/</a><p>

Provides information on solvent and process alternatives for parts cleaning
and degreasing. Includes a comprehensive listing of existing and new cleaning technologies, ideas for minimizing waste, listing of state technical assistance providers, and a process conversion checklist.<p>      

<strong>EPA Office of Air Pollution Prevention Programs (Green Star, etc)</strong><br>
access:       <a href="http://www.epa.gov/docs/GCDOAR/OAR-APPD.html">http://www.epa.gov/docs/GCDOAR/OAR-APPD.html</a><p>

<strong>National Pollution Prevention Center for Higher Education (NPPC)</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.umich.edu/~nppcpub/nppc.html">http://www.umich.edu/~nppcpub/nppc.html</a><p>

Created by US EPA and based at the University of Michigan, NPPC collects,
develops, and disseminates educational materials on pollution prevention.  The target audience is primarily academia. <p>

<a name="Energy"></a>
<h3>Department of Energy (DOE)</h3>

<strong>Alternative Fuels Data Center (AFDC) - National Renewable Energy Laboratory, U.S. Department of Energy</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.afdc.nrel.gov">http://www.afdc.nrel.gov/</a><p>

The AFDC collects operating information from vehicles (in programs sponsored by the Alternative Motor Fuels Act) running on alternative fuels, analyzes those data, and makes them available to the public.  Data is also available for the Biofuels Information Center and the Clean Cities program.<p>

<strong>Ames Laboratory Environmental Technology Development (ETD)</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.edt.ameslab.gov">http://www.edt.ameslab.gov/</a><p>

As part of the U.S. Department of Energy, Ames Laboratory ETD is developing
technological solutions to the problems of contamination resulting from
nuclear weapons production.  Features of this site include a library and
Internet "Green" Pages.<p>

<strong>U.S. Department of Energy (DOE)--Energy Efficiency and Renewable Energy Network </strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.eren.doe.gov">http://www.eren.doe.gov/</a><p>

Offers hundreds of pages of information from the Office of Energy Efficiency and Renewable Energy.  This online library of resources offers news and archives about conservation techniques and developments in the world of energy technology.  A search engine is provided.<p>

<strong>U.S. Department of Energy (DOE) Office of Environmental Management (EM)</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.em.doe.gov/index.html">http://www.em.doe.gov/index.html</a><p>

This DOE site features information and links to environmental management and pollution prevention at DOE.  A direct link to pollution prevention information can be accessed with: <a href="http://www.em.doe.gov/polprev.html">http://www.em.doe.gov/polprev.html</a><p>

<strong>EPIC (Energy Pollution Prevention Information Clearinghouse)</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://146.138.5.107/EPIC.EXE?EPIC">http://146.138.5.107/EPIC.EXE?EPIC</a><p>

The purpose of EPIC is to facilitate the exchange of U.S. DOE pollution prevention information between DOE sites, state and local governments, and private industries. It includes a file listing of DOE-specific P2 information and a calendar of upcoming DOE-sponsored conferences, meetings, and training events related to pollution prevention.<p>  

<strong>Office of Industrial Technologies (OIT) Home Page (U.S. Department of Energy)</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.nrel.gov/oit/oit.html">http://www.nrel.gov/oit/oit.html</a><p>

OIT is part of the U.S. Department of Energy's Office of Energy Efficiency and Renewable Energy.  It creates partnerships among industry, trade groups, government agencies, and other organizations to research, develop, and deliver advanced energy efficiency, renewable energy, and pollution prevention technologies for industrial customers.  <p>

<strong>Office of Industrial Technologies (OIT) Chemicals Industry Team</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.nrel.gov/oit/Industries-of-the-Future/chemical.html">http://www.nrel.gov/oit/Industries-of-the-Future/chemical.html</a><p>

As part of OIT's Industries of the Future strategy, the Chemicals Industry
Team was established as a partnership between OIT and the U.S. chemical
industry to maximize economic, energy, and environmental benefits through
research and development of innovative technologies. <p> 

<strong>U.S. Department of Energy's Technical Information Services (TIS) </strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://venus.hyperk.com/abouttis.html">http://venus.hyperk.com/abouttis.html</a><p>

The Environment, Safety, and Health (ES&H) Technical Information Services
(TIS) is a computer-based information system designed for safety and health
professionals.  Several databases are on TIS including Safety Performance
Measurement System (SPMS), OSHA standards, and ES&H technical publications. <p>

<a name="Commerce"></a>
<h3>Department of Commerce</h3>

<strong>U.S. Department of Commerce</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.doc.gov/CommerceHomePage.html">http://www.doc.gov/CommerceHomePage.html</a><p>

Information and links to economic development, technology transfer, and
technology development. <p>

<strong>National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST)</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.nist.gov">http://www.nist.gov/</a><p>

An agency of the U.S. Department of Commerce, NIST's primary mission is to
promote U.S. economic growth by working with industry to develop and apply
technology, measurements, and standards. Information at this site includes
thegrassroots Manufacturing Extension Partnership and Advanced Technology
Program.  <p>

<strong>National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST)-Manufacturing extension Program</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.mep.nist.gov">http://www.mep.nist.gov/</a><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.tecnet.org">http://www.tecnet.org/</a><p>

<a name="Misc Federal Govt WWW Sites"></a>
<h3>Miscellaneous Federal Government WWW Sites</h3>

<strong>Cornell University Archive of Federal Regulations</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.law.cornell.edu/topics/environmental.html">http://www.law.cornell.edu/topics/environmental.html</a><p>

<strong>Internet Virtual Library - Environmental Law</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.law.indiana.edu/law/intenvlaw.html">http://www.law.indiana.edu/law/intenvlaw.html</a><p>

<strong>MSDS On-line</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="gopher://gopher.chem.utah.edu /11/MSDS">gopher://gopher.chem.utah.edu/11/MSDS</a><p>

<strong>Code of Federal Regulations (CFR)</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.pls.com:8001/his/cfr.html">http://www.pls.com:8001/his/cfr.html</a><p>

Provides basic information about the CFR along with an online service for searching the CFR.  However, if you wish to use this for legal research, it is recommended that you verify your results with the printed Code of Federal Regulations.<p>

<strong>Envirogate (Environmental Technology Gateway)</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://iridium.nttc.edu/environmental.html">http://iridium.nttc.edu/environmental.html</a><p>

As part of the National Technology Transfer Center (NTTC) home page, Envirogate contains news, programs, technologies, and resources--including Web links to many other environmental sites.<p>

<strong>Environmental Pollution and Control </strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.fedworld.gov/environ.htm">http://www.fedworld.gov/environ.htm</a><p>

A division of FedWorld, this site features links to various governmental agencies and laboratories.<p>

<strong>Federal Register--Daily Table of Contents</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://earth1.epa.gov:80/EPAFR-CONTENTS">http://earth1.epa.gov:80/EPAFR-CONTENTS/</a><p>

The complete table of contents for the Federal Register.<p>  

<strong>Federal Register--EPA Environmental Subset</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.epa.gov/Rules.html">http://www.epa.gov/Rules.html</a><p>

Contains the full-text of selected Federal Register documents that deal with the environment or environment-related issues.<p>
 
<strong>FedWorld</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.fedworld.gov">http://www.fedworld.gov</a><p>

A one-stop location for locating and ordering U.S. government information<p>

<strong>Global Network for Environmental Technology</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://gnet.together.org">http://gnet.together.org/</a><p>

Provides information about the Clinton Administration's goal towards
establishing a public-private partnership to advance the development and
diffusion of environmental technologies. <p>

<strong>National Technology Transfer Center (NTTC)</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.nttc.edu">http://www.nttc.edu/</a><p>

NTTC is the hub of a national network linking U.S. companies with federal
laboratories to turn government research results into practical, commercially-relevant technology.  Features include:  gateways to federal laboratories and governmental agencies, and bulletin board services and databases relating to technology transfer.<p>

<strong>Oak Ridge National Laboratory Energy Efficiency and Renewable Energy Program</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.ornl.gov/Energy_Eff/Energy_Eff.html">http://www.ornl.gov/ORNL/Energy_Eff/Energy_Eff.html</a><p>

Conducts research and development in the field of sustainable energy
technology.  Features descriptions and news about their programs; also
contains search engines and databases.<p>

<strong>Oak Ridge National Laboratory Environmental Sciences Division (ESD)</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.esd.ornl.gov">http://www.esd.ornl.gov/</a><p>

A research laboratory which focuses on how the development and use of energy affect the environment.  An online publications listing is available.<p>

<strong>Sandia National Laboratory</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.sandia.gov/agil/home_page.html">http://www.sandia.gov/agil/home_page.html</a><p>

Allows government, industry, and academia to access and exchange information on the latest developments in agile and advanced manufacturing.  Companies and organizations already participating in the site include Honeywell, General Electric, and University of California-Berkeley.<p>

<strong>U.S. Army Corps of Engineers</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.usace.army.mil/.index.html">http://www.usace.army.mil/.index.html</a><p>

Information about the Corps.<p>

<strong>U.S. Geological Survey</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.usgs.gov">http://www.usgs.gov/</a><p>

USGS is the nation's largest earth-science research and information agency. 
Their Web site features fact sheets, information releases, publications
listings, and data products.<p>


