<a name="International"><hr></a>
<h3>International</h3>


<strong>Australian Environment</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://kaos.erin.gov.au">http://kaos.erin.gov.au/</a><p>

A project of the Australian Department of the Environment, this site includes information on cleaner production and energy efficiency.<p>

<strong>Ecologica E-TIP Database</strong><br>
Access        <a href="http://ecologia.nier.org/index.html">http://ecologia.nier.org/index.html</a><p>

<strong>Environment Canada, Atlantic Region</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.ns.doe.ca/how.html">http://www.ns.doe.ca/how.html</a><p>

Provides information on Canada's environmental policies and programs including P2)<p>

<strong>Environment Canada's P2 Home Page</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.ns.doe.ca/epb/progs/pollprev.html">http://www.ns.doe.ca/epb/progs/pollprev.html</a><p>

<strong>National Cleaner Production Database (Australia) </strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://kaos.erin.gov/human_env/industry/ACPD2.html">http://kaos.erin.gov.au/human_env/industry/ACPD2.html</a><p>

Provides case study information on cleaner production measures used in a wide variety of industries in Austrialia.  Database targets small to medium-sized businesses.  Also see: <a href="http://kais.erin.gov.au/human_env/industry/ACPD.html">http://kaos.erin.gov.au/human_env/industry/ACPD.html</a><p>

<strong>United Nations Environment Programme (UNEP)</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://unep.unep.no">http://unep.unep.no/</a><p>

UNEP coordinates environmental policies within the UN system and encourages
environmental protection throughout the world.  Includes information on
sustainable resource management and environmental economics.<p>



<a name="Business & Industry"><hr></a>
<h3>Business & Industry</h3>


<strong>CAMP (Cleveland Advanced Manufacturing Program)</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.edrc.cmu.edu:8888/acorn/demos/CAMP/camp.html">http://www.edrc.cmu.edu:8888/acorn/demos/CAMP/camp.html</a><p>

CAMP supports manufacturers in the Great Lakes region by providing research, technology development and deployment, training and business assistance.  As of 09/06/95, this site has only limited access (it's under construction).  The site should be improved within 2 months. <p>

<strong>Chrysler</strong><br>
Access:       <a href="http://www.chrylsercorp.com/environmentl">http://www.chryslercorp.com/environment/</a><p>

Provides information on Chrysler's recycling & conservation programs, and on the company's efforts in building flexible-fuel vehicles.<p>

<strong>Ciba-Geigy</strong><br>
Access:       http://www.ciba.com/cc/safetyenvir.html<p>

Provides a policy statement about the company's commitment to environmental responsibility.<p>

<strong>Electronics Manufacturing Productivity Facility</strong><br>
Access:       http://www.engr.uipui.edu/empf/<p>

The Navy National Center of Excellence for electronics manufacturing, EMPF facilitates cooperation between government, industry, and academia to develop and transfer manufacturing technologies to increase domestic productivity in electronics manufacturing.<p>

<strong>Environmental Resource Center (ERC)</strong><br>
Access:       http://ftp.clearlake.ibm.com/ERC/overview.html<p>

ERC is an innovative cooperative between private industry and government. Directed and developed by industry, ERC finds, identifies, accesses, catalogs, and integrates existing environmental information sources.<p>

<strong>Finishing.com, the Home Page of the Finishing Industry</strong><br>
Access:       http://www.finishing.com/<p>

All about surface finishing, from anodizing to powder coating. <p>

<strong>Ford Motor Co. Recycling</strong><br>
Access:       http://www.ford.com/corporate-info/environment/Recycling.html<p>

Information on Ford's automotive recycling program.<p>

<strong>IBM</strong><br>
Access:       http://www.clearlake.ibm.com/ETS/<p>

Information and policies about IBM's environmental commitments.<p>

<strong>Industry.Net (On-Line Marketplace)</strong><br>
Access:       http://www.industry.net<p>

A shopping mall for the manufacturing industry where shoppers can communicate with vendors. Features an online directory of 180,000 U.S. manufacturers.<p>  

<strong>Institute of Advanced Manufacturing Sciences (IAMS)</strong><br>
Access:       http://www.iams.org<p>

(Should be available by 09/15/95)<p>

<strong>Monsanto</strong><br>
Access:       http://www.monsanto.com:80/environ.html<p>

General environmental policy statement.<p>

<strong>NORTEL Habitat (Northern Telecom)</strong><br>
Access:       http://www.nortel.com:80/english/environ/habitat.html<p>

An online platform for corporate environmental issues.  Browsers can obtain
information ranging from international environmental standards to measuring a company's environmentalism. <p>

<strong>Petroleum Technology Transfer Council (PTTC)</strong><br>
Access:       http://www.msc.edu/pttc/<p>

PTTC was formed by the U.S. oil and gas exploration and production (E&P)
industry to improve technology transfer to producers. It facilitates the
transfer of E&P technologies for uses in areas like environmental compliance.<p>

<strong>Ribbon-Jet Tech, Online Printer Cartridge Recycling Instructions</strong><br>
Access:       http://ie.uwindsor.ca/ecdm_info/recycle.html<p>

A Colorado company that supplies information as to how to recycle printer
ribbons, ink jet cartridges, and some Laser Jet toner cartridges.<p>

<strong>Thomas Register of American Manufacturers</strong><br>
Access:       http://www.thomasregister.com:8000<p>

A database for product and service suppliers in 52,000 categories.  Includes an online supply finder.<p>

<strong>United Technologies</strong><br>
Access:       http://www.utc.com/<p>

Provides information on the corporation's environmental policies and programs, and applications of P2 in its manufacturing programs.<p>




<a name="Pollution Prevention Research & Information Centers"><hr></a>
<h3>Pollution Prevention Research & Information Centers</h3>

<strong>Center for Technology Transfer and Pollution Prevention (CT2P2)</strong><br>
Access:       http://ingis.acn.purdue.edu:9999/cttpp/cttpp.html<p>

The CT2P2 has developed a series of over 30 PC-based computer programs on various aspects of the environment and pollution prevention.  These programs can be downloaded and include topics on groundwater education, management of domestic wastes, and pesticide storage.<p>

<strong>Energy Analysis and Diagnostic Center (EADC)--Industrial Assessment Database at Rutgers University</strong><br>
Access:       http://128.6.70.23/<p>

This site contains databases and other information relating to pollution
prevention including an industrial assessment database.<p>

<strong>Green Engineering WWW Servers (Environmentally Conscious Design & Manufacturing Lab)</strong><br>
Access:       http://ie.uwindsor.ca/other_green.html<p>

A listing of academic sites and research centers related to environmentally
conscious design and manufacturing.<p>

<strong>Hazardous Waste Research and Information Center (HWRIC)</strong><br>
Access:       http://www.inhs.uiuc.edu/hwric/hmlhome.html<p>

A division of Illinois' nonregulatory environmental agency, the Department of Energy and Natural Resources, HWRIC services include clean manufacturing and pollution prevention technical assistance. An online publications listing is available.<p>

<strong>National Environmental Information Resources Center (NEIRC)</strong><br>
Access:       http://gwis.circ.gwu.edu/~greenu/neirc.html<p>

Provides one-stop  access to a broad range of environmental information including P2 and environmentally concious manufacturing.  Participants include US Green Building Council and Public Technology, Inc. <p>

<strong>National Pollution Prevention Roundtable (NPPR) Pollution Prevention Yellow Pages</strong><br>
Access:  http://wastenot.inel.gov:80/envirosense/program/regional/rndtable/index.html<p>

This is an update to the Directory of State and Local Pollution Prevention Programs, published in 1992.  Provides a listing of organizations and contacts which are sorted by state.<p>    

<strong>Pacific Northwest Pollution Prevention Research Center (PPRC) Pollution Prevention Research Projects Database</strong><br>
Access:       gopher://gopher.pnl.gov:2070/1/.pprc<p>

While primarily a focused on the Pacific Northwest, PPRC provides information on pollution prevention research activities and funding opportunities throughout the U.S.  Includes a publications listing.  <p>

<strong>P2Tech - Pollution Prevention Archive</strong><br>
Access:       http://gopher.great-lakes.net:2200/1s/glin/majordomo/p2tech<p>

Provides access to P2 files on a variety of subjects.  However, these are not in hypertext.<p>

<strong>Tellus Institute</strong><br>
Access:       http://www.channel1.com:80/users/tellus/tellus.html (that's the number 1 after channel)<p>

A non-profit research and consulting organization devoted to resource
management and environmental issues.  Includes P2 information on total cost
assessment and life-cycle assessment.<p>
  
<strong>Toxic Use Reduction Institute (TURI) P2GEMS</strong><br>
Access:       http://www.uml.edu/turi/<p>

<strong>UC Berkeley's Center for Green Design and Manufacturing</strong><br>
Access:       http://euler.berkeley.edu/green/cgdm.html<p>

Provides up-to-date information on UCB's Green Design program, which focuses on software and other design tools for the manufacturing industry. Summaries of past publications, current work and upcoming papers are provided.<p>

<strong>UCLA's Center for Clean Technology (CCT)</strong><br>
Access:       http://cct.seas.ucla.edu/<p>

This site provides an overview of CCT's research programs.  Pollution
prevention research includes a strong focus on process industries and chemical engineering.<p>

<strong>University of North Dakota:  Energy and Environmental Research Center (EERC)</strong><br>
Access:       http://www.eerc.und.nodak.edu<p>

The EERC specializes in clean, efficient energy technologies and environmental systems that prevent pollution and clean up contaminated air, soil, and water.<p>

<strong>University of Wiscosnin-Solid and Hazardous Waste Education Center</strong><br>
Access: http://gopher.great-lakes.net:2200/1/partners/shwec<p>

Describes SHWEC programming activities and lists vaialble pollution prevention fact sheets and other resources.<p>

