<H2>Spring 1996</H2>
</CENTER>
<hr>

<h3>Students Selected for Summer Energy Internships</h3>

Twenty Illinois high school students will have a special opportunity to gain valuable work experience in energy related programs this summer. The students were selected from 47 very well qualified applicants to serve two-month internships in the Energy Intern Program which pays $850/month.  The intern program provides high school junior and senior students an opportunity to work in a professional environment and carry out research projects and other activities. Funding for the 20 students comes from the Illinois Department of Commerce and Community Affairs.<p>

ILEED is pleased to announce the following interns and host organizations:<p>

<pre> 
