<h3>Congratulations - ILEED Award Winning Schools</h3>

On May 1, 1996, over 250 students and teachers representing 60 schools throughout Illinois were recognized for their outstanding efforts in energy and environmental education at the ILEED Youth Awards for Energy Achievement Program. Director Dennis Whetstone of the Illlinois Department of Commerce and Community Affairs (DCCA) honored these students and teachers with hand-painted plaques at a luncheon at the Renaissance Hotel in Springfield. Many stayed in Springfield to tour the State Capitol and meet with their local Representatives.<p>

Director Whetstone is very proud of the energy/environmental impact these students and teachers have made in their schools and communities. Because of their outstanding efforts, Illinois is a leader in the country in energy/environmental education.<p>

