<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>DCCA: Proposed Rules - November 15, 1996</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000080" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#8080C0" ALINK="#8080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/logosm.jpg" alt="DCCA Logo" width=165 height=82 align=left>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<h3>
Department of Commerce & Community Affairs<p>
</h3>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<font size=+3>Proposed Rules</font>
<hr>

<CENTER>
The proposed rules marked with an * are of particular interest to small
business and the department specifically requests comments on those issues.
Comments on any rule are encouraged.<P>
</CENTER>
<HR>
<h3 align=center>
Illinois Register<BR>
November 15, 1996
</h3>
<hr>

<h4>DEPARTMENT ON AGING</h4>

<strong><em>Elder Rights</em></strong> - Implements the Long Term Care Obbudsman Program.  (New)<p>

<strong><em>Older Americans Act Program</em></strong> - Repealed and addressed above.<p>

<hr>
<h4>ILLINOIS COMMUNITY COLLEGE BOARD</h4>

<strong><em>Administration of the Illinois Public Community College Act</em></strong> - Criteria and procedures for implementing three initiatives grants (education-to-careers; student support services; and, technology support).<p>

<hr>
<h4>DEPARTMENT OF NUCLEAR SAFETY</h4>

<strong><em>Licensing Requirements for Source Material Milling Facilities</em></strong> - Updates federal regulations; adds incorporations by reference; deletes certain definitions; reflects current standards; clean-up language for consistency.<p>

<hr>
<h4>DEPARTMENT OF PROFESSIONAL REGULATION</h4>

<strong><em>Private Detective, Private Alarm and Private Security  Act of 1993*</em></strong> - Establishes requirements and procedures for obtaining a locksmith license.  (Statutory)<p>

<hr>
<h4>DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC HEALTH</h4>

<strong><em>Structural Pest Control Code*</em></strong> - Establishes regulations for protecting potable water well supplies and groundwater at commercial structural pest control business locations where pesticides may be stored within setback zones and regulated recharge areas established under EPA.<p>

<hr>
<h4>DEPARTMENT OF REVENUE</h4>

<strong><em>Electronic Filing of Illinois Individual Income Tax Returns*</em></strong> - Provides for direct deposit by the Department of income tax refunds into taxpayers' accounts.<p> 
 

